<p>The Mallard Conditional Processing extension provides a standard mechanism
for run-time conditional processing. Using XPath-based tests with extension
functions, you can include or exclude certain content based on criteria such
as the user's current environment.</p>

<p>Conditional processing is done by the <code xref="if_test">test</code>
attribute, which takes an XPath expression. The expression must evaluate to
true for the affected content to be displayed.</p>

